<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written submission from Astute Technical Services Ltd</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:18pt 0pt 4.5pt 36pt; text-align:center; text-indent:-36pt"><a name="_Toc369879836"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written submission from Astute Technical Services Ltd </span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">I watched the on line video of your recent select committee interview of the operators of the electrical</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> safety schemes with some concern.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">For your information I am an electrical engineer not an electrician who inspects and tests electrical installation both domestic and commercial. I </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">am the appointed inspector for two local authorities carrying out inspections of domestic installations for </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">Part P compliance. I also carry out inspections of electrical installations as an expert witness for Trading Standards and appear in the criminal court to prosecute offenders in addition to appearing in the County Court in civil matters. I am also a part t</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">ime lecturer at a college teaching the regulations, inspection and test and the design of electrical installations. I am registered with the NICEIC as an Approved Contractor and I am also a member of the Institution of Engineering and Technology. I am not </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">an electrician and I do not engage in electrical installation work in order I can be unbiased and independent. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">Having watched the video and listened to the questions and answers I believe that your committee may not be aware of some of the issues concerni</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">ng Part P of the Building Regulations.</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">The electrical Competent Person Scheme is a “Competent Person Scheme” in name only. The schemes register companies where one person in the company has undergone an assessment of competence. That assessment in a lot of</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> cases is at best very minimal.</span></li><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">These registered companies can, and do, then send unqualified and incompetent persons to people’s houses to carry out the installation work. On competition the work should be inspected and tested by a competent person. This </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">is not always done.</span></li><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">think if a householder knows about part P and takes the time and trouble to select a Competent Person scheme operator they no doubt have a reasonable belief a competent person will turn up on the doorstep to do the work. In many case</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">s they stand as much chance of getting a competent person as asking a bloke down the pub to do the job.</span></li><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">If Part P has had any impact on public safety it is minimal and not measurable. If you examine the DCLGs published statistics on fires in premises the c</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">onsiderable decline in fires in both commercial premises and dwellings started before the implementation of Part P.</span></li><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">The honest decent electrician was already working to a reasonable standard without Part P. Those persons probably have joined a competent pe</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">rson scheme and are paying effectively a tax on their business to work. They have to compete in a very comparative </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">market place with non-competent contractors sporting the competent person scheme logos, un-registered electricians and cowboys. Most househo</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">lders choose their electricians on price and have little knowledge of competent person schemes. </span></li><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">It was not mentioned at your meeting by anyone but there is already a central on line register of competent persons here </span><a href="http://www.competentperson.co.uk/"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:11pt">http://www.competentperson.co.uk/</span></a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">. I think this is maintained by DCLG but I am not sure.</span></li><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">Mr Bruno unfortunately did not mention that the NAPIT ElectricSafe register permits a member of any of competent person schemes to register. It is an inclu</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">sive register. The Certsure register in not inclusive and only has companies registered with one of their companies.</span></li><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">I thought Mr Bruno was unfairly outnumbered at the meeting as the single representative from NAPIT. The Electrical Safety Council, NICEIC, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">ECA, Elecsa, Ascertiva are all part of one organisation Certsure who fielded 3 persons at the meeting. For your information and for the avoidance of doubt I am not a member of NAPIT and I have no financial interest in that company.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">Should you require any m</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">ore information in connection with Part P I would be happy to give you an unbiased honest answer rather than the smoke and mirrors you have been hearing. Although it would be professional suicide for me, as I would be treated as a whistle blowe</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">, I would b</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">e prepared to appear before your select committee and answer any questions they may have. I would however be happier and more comfortable to meet you in private and answer your questions.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>